The Central Shaft of Blood Shoal
    The stone wall circling the central shaft of this underwater city is
perfectly smooth, a lasting testament to the abilities of the civilization
that bored through the solid bedrock. A series of ancient runes runs along
the surface of the stone wall in a spiral that gradually descends towards
the bottom of the shaft. The ancient runes glow brightly, bathing the area
with an eerie red light. A number of round openings in the walls provide
access to tunnels that lead into different parts of the ancient city.

A Scratched Stone Intersection
    The stone surfaces of this large intersection were once quite smooth,
but heavy traffic by countless sahuagin swimming by has left thousands of
scratches on the stone. Although the rough-walled intersection seems to be
part of a residential area, it is remarkably free of clutter, except for a
few small piles of dung in the corners. Wide corridors extend to the north
and east from here, while a thin silver gate in the western wall controls
access to a large sahuagin home. The central shaft of the city lies just
to the south of here, through a perfectly round opening.

A Crude Stone Chamber
    Lying just off the central shaft of the underwater city, this expansive
stone chamber looks like it has been freshly cut from the stone. The crude
carving is clearly the work of enormous clawed beasts, and no one has taken
the time to finish smoothing the walls. To the west and south of here lie
smaller chambers filled with junk that appear to be for sale, while the rest
of the underwater city can be reached through the shaft to the east.

The Central Shaft of Blood Shoal
    The stone wall circling the central shaft of this underwater city is
perfectly smooth, a lasting testament to the abilities of the civilization
that bored through the solid bedrock. A series of ancient runes runs along
the surface of the stone wall in a spiral that gradually descends towards
the bottom of the shaft. The ancient runes glow brightly, bathing the area
with an eerie red light. A number of round openings in the walls provide
access to tunnels that lead into different parts of the ancient city.

    The stone wall circling the central shaft of this underwater city is
perfectly smooth, a lasting testament to the abilities of the civilization

    The stone wall circling the central shaft of this underwater city is
perfectly smooth, a lasting testament to the abilities of the civilization
that bored through the solid bedrock. A series of ancient runes runs along
the surface of the stone wall in a spiral that gradually descends towards

Inside a Massive Bronze Cage
    The thick bronze bars enclosing this massive cage are covered with deep
scratches. They look like they have been beaten and abused by a family of
ferocious beasts blessed with gigantic claws. Somehow, the bars have stood
up to the constant abuse and prevented the angry beasts digging out through
the surrounding stone. The solid bronze plates forming the floor and roof
are also warped and scratched, and it's a small wonder that this cage still
remains intact. The massive cage continues into the darkness to the north,
and a sturdy bronze grate separates it from a shadowy alcove above.

A Shadowy Stone Chamber

    Dancing shadows cling to the large chamber's ancient stone walls. Near
the far eastern wall, there is a massive throne-like chair crafted from an
assortment of dolphin and whale bones set upon a dais. Random bits of gold

The Central Shaft of Blood Shoal
    The stone wall circling the central shaft of this underwater city is
perfectly smooth, a lasting testament to the abilities of the civilization
that bored through the solid bedrock. A series of ancient runes runs along
the surface of the stone wall in a spiral that gradually descends towards

Beneath the Main Mast
    Here towards the front of the ship main mast rises out of the deck like
an enormous vallenwood tree reaching for the sky. On a sloop, the main mast
is placed forward of the center of the ship to give it more maneuverability
in the water. The salty smell of the ocean is refreshing, and a brisk ocean
breeze blows by as the ship cuts swiftly through the waves. Some thick rope
ladders hang down from the main mast, allowing sailors to climb up the mast
to tend to the sails, while a narrow opening in the deck provides access to
a wooden ladder which leads the hold down below.
A sleek lead golem, Mhurrd, stands here, expressionless.

    Here towards the front of the ship main mast rises out of the deck like
an enormous vallenwood tree reaching for the sky. On a sloop, the main mast
is placed forward of the center of the ship to give it more maneuverability

ladders hang down from the main mast, allowing sailors to climb up the mast

Beneath the Main Mast

    Here towards the front of the ship main mast rises out of the deck like
an enormous vallenwood tree reaching for the sky. On a sloop, the main mast
is placed forward of the center of the ship to give it more maneuverability
in the water. The salty smell of the ocean is refreshing, and a brisk ocean
breeze blows by as the ship cuts swiftly through the waves. Some thick rope
ladders hang down from the main mast, allowing sailors to climb up the mast
to tend to the sails, while a narrow opening in the deck provides access to
a wooden ladder which leads the hold down below.
The corpse of a young pirate is lying here. [3]

In the Ship's Hold
    The air down here in the hold of the ship is quite musty, and the smell

of manure wafts in from the aft part of the hold. Clumps of damp hay have

been scattered across the floor to try and help cover up the smell. On each
side of the ship, cannons in various states of repair aim out through the
portholes, ready to blast giant holes in the hulls of enemy ships. Towards
the front of the hold, a simple table flanked by five-legged stools must be
what passes for a galley here. A wooden ladder leads up to the main deck.

The Stern of the Ship
    This area of the ship is known as the poop deck since it is build upon
the roof of the captain's quarters. From this high vantage point, sailors
can see for miles off into the distance. The powerful winds reflecting off
the giant sails up above buffet this area at the back of the ship. Sturdy
railing wraps around the perimeter of the platform, giving people something
to hold on to and prevent them from accidentally falling overboard whenever
the ship changes direction. The long blue boards of the poop deck continue
back towards the helm of the ship where the ship's wheel stands.
